What Kathryn Hinds is trying to say is that the Andres were able to build a great civilization even though the Andres Mountians weren't the best habitat at that moment. In source #3 "The Lost City", it said that the architecture and the stone work are of the best quality. The Anasazi used anything available in their environment to meet their needs in society. In the text "Artifacts Gallery", it talks about the Anasazi using a plant called Yucca as their food source. The Yucca Plant was also used for soap, shampoo, mats, rope, belts, and many more daily needs.The aurthor of the 2nd source is trying to tell us that the Anazanzi would use anything that was given to them to survive. They also used baskets for many things like cooking and it was a bonus because the baskets they made could hold water and tolerate heat. At least that's what the 2nd Sources says. In conclusion, the Anasazi would use anything in their environment to meet their needs as a society.

The Machu Picchu and the Mesa Verde are two different cliff dwellings. They may be different but they're sure some similarities with these two societies. These two societies are located in two different places, which means that they had to go through different struggles while living in their environment. These are some of the differences and similarities of the two historic societies. 

 

   Mesa Verde ("green table" in Spanish) is located in what we know today as Colorado. Mesa Verde was around from A.D. 550 to A.D. 1300 according to Robin Chalmers. The people from Mesa Verde, the Anasazis, didn't go extinct. As a matter of a fact, it's been a mystery on where they could have been after the 20 year drought that made them decide that they could leave Mesa Verde. Before the disappearance of the Anasazis, I'm going to tell you about their life and how they manage to use the things around them to get their needs for their survival. The Anasazis would make baskets, and they weren't only used to collect foods like seeds, nuts, fruits,and berries; they were also used to to hold water and it was able to tolerate the heat.These baskets were used for many things and not only for food gathering and liquid holding. The Anasazins would also use Yucca plants for apparel and for food source. They would make footwear, rope,mats,belts and baskets from Yucca plants. These people used everything they were able to get their hands on for their need. They had a small amount of resources, but they made a good use out of them.

 

  The Andres Mountains of Western South Africa, are where the Incas were located not so long ago. They lived in a harsh environment with a small amount of oxygen, and with only 2% of the land was farmable. The Incas civilization didn't mind, they were able to make a GREAT civilization. Their architecture and stone work were the best quality. The Incas established thousand of miles of roads to link their vast empire. Like I said before, the Incas didn't have as much framing advantages, they were often low on soil and frequent droughts would happen. Their farming wasn't the best framing specially for a civilization like theirs. Even if they were good at building, they had a disadvantage in framing.

 

  These two societies, both had advantages and disadvantages. The Incas had the best building skills, but their farming wasn't the best, unlike the Anasazis, they had a good advantage on framing, and not so much on construction. With this in our heads, we know that the Incas, didn't have much resources as the Anasazis. In my facts about the Anasaziz, I said that they would use the Yucca plant for many things like footwear and food, and since the Incas didn't live in the right destination, that prevented them form having advantages like the Anasazis. These two societies had very different environments and they had different struggles to deal with. I admire these two societies because they were given resources and they took them and made a living out of them. I hope you guys enjoyed my facts about these two societies.
